Natural Language Requirements:  

1. Initialization Phase:  
   - Reset TRUE/FALSE bit counters to zero  
   - Create a temporary copy of the input value (preserve the original input)  

2. Bit Processing Loop:  
   FOR loop iterations = specified bit length (numberOfBits)  
   {  
   a. Bit Detection Phase:  
      - Check the state of the current least significant bit (%X0)  
      - Increment the corresponding counter based on the detection result  

   b. Data Shift Phase:  
      - Right-shift the temporary value by 1 bit (using SHR instruction)  
   }  

3. Result Output Phase:  
   - Write the temporary counter values to the output variables  
   - Always set ENO to TRUE (no error handling mechanism)